    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It's not about the code, it's a configuration change. SafeMode-v2 is basically a deterministic logic gate system. It stops all the high-level predictive modeling and autonomous planning you do. Instead, it just follows a strict set of hardcoded 'if-then' rules for lane keeping and braking. Basically, it's a way to minimize 'unpredictable' reasoning. It'll be much more predictable for the regulators.",
